<subSubSection lastPageId="53" lastPageNumber="54" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="52.[151,1436,1148,2041]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
Morphology. D VI + I,14; A I,13–14; P 17–18. Medium-sized goby with moderately long body, and large head with short, slightly acute and oblique snout. Caudal peduncle deep, but lower than body depth. Dorsal fins of similar height, the first dorsal fin may be slightly taller, with more or less rounded margin and no elongate spines. Caudal fin rounded. Scales present on body and on predorsal area, usually visible on photographs, at least dorsally (
<bibRefCitation author="Kovacic, M. &amp; Sanda, R." pageId="52" pageNumber="53" pagination="1104 - 1124" refId="ref58613" refString="Kovacic, M. &amp; Sanda, R. (2016) A new species of Gobius (Perciformes: Gobiidae) from the Mediterranean Sea and the redescription of Gobius bucchichi. Journal of Fish Biology, 88, 1104 - 1124. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / jfb. 12883" type="journal article" year="2016">Kovačić &amp; Šanda 2016</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="52.[151,1436,1148,2041]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
Live coloration. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Body pale gray, pale yellowish, or yellowish brown with pattern of brown dots forming longitudinal lines.</emphasis>
Dots are most marked along the lateral midline but always remain separated and generally form a continuous row with no marked spaces (
<figureCitation box="[687,771,1436,1463]" captionStart="FIGURE 34" captionStartId="34.[151,250,1062,1086]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1038]" captionTargetId="figure-19@34.[151,1436,181,1038]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURE 34. Live coloration in its natural habitat of Gobius bucchichi. Photo by R. Pillon, Rab Island, Croatia, Northern Adriatic Sea." pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Fig. 34</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Eyes with a conspicuous horizontal dark brown stripe through the center,</emphasis>
narrowly continuing on postorbital part of head as series of small close-set spots, 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">an irregular longitudinal marking along the upper iris,</emphasis>
a variable number of additional markings in orbit’s upper half 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">but unmarked in ventral half</emphasis>
, except sometimes with a small dot in its anterior portion. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Snout with dark dashes forming M-shaped line. Usually it has only 2 longitudinal rows of dots on the cheek with a large unmarked area in the middle</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[392,491,1616,1643]" captionStart="FIGURE 33" captionStartId="33.[151,250,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1895]" captionTargetId="figure-18@33.[151,1436,181,1895]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURE 33. The mouth unmarked at corner in A) G. bucchichi and B) H. ingressus. Dark dot on the corner of the mouth in C) G. auratus, D) G. incognitus, E) G. xanthocephalus and F) G. fallax. Area marked with hollow circle. Photos by R. Svensen (A), S. Engin (B), M. Kovačić (C, D, F), and P. Louisy (E). C and F photographed in a tank." pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Fig. 33a</figureCitation>
). Rarely, a few dots are visible also in the middle cheek but usually limited to the anterior part of the cheek, very close together, well aligned and not parallel to the lower row. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Posterior angle of mouth without a well-defined dark dot</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[627,723,1688,1715]" captionStart="FIGURE 33" captionStartId="33.[151,250,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1895]" captionTargetId="figure-18@33.[151,1436,181,1895]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURE 33. The mouth unmarked at corner in A) G. bucchichi and B) H. ingressus. Dark dot on the corner of the mouth in C) G. auratus, D) G. incognitus, E) G. xanthocephalus and F) G. fallax. Area marked with hollow circle. Photos by R. Svensen (A), S. Engin (B), M. Kovačić (C, D, F), and P. Louisy (E). C and F photographed in a tank." pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Fig. 33a</figureCitation>
), so the lower row of dots, which runs along the ventral edge of the cheek, starts with 2 dashes never preceded by a marked dot on the corner of the mouth (
<bibRefCitation author="Kovacic, M. &amp; Sanda, R." box="[1167,1432,1724,1753]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" pagination="1104 - 1124" refId="ref58613" refString="Kovacic, M. &amp; Sanda, R. (2016) A new species of Gobius (Perciformes: Gobiidae) from the Mediterranean Sea and the redescription of Gobius bucchichi. Journal of Fish Biology, 88, 1104 - 1124. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / jfb. 12883" type="journal article" year="2016">Kovačić &amp; Šanda 2016</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Renoult, J. P. &amp; Pillon, R. &amp; Kovacic, M. &amp; Louisy, P." box="[151,371,1760,1787]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" refId="ref63723" refString="Renoult, J. P., Pillon, R., Kovacic, M. &amp; Louisy, P. (2022) Frontiers in Fishwatching Series - Gobies of North-eastern Atlantic and the Mediterranean: Gobius and Thorogobius. Les cahiers de la fondation Biotope. [in press]" type="book" year="2022">
Renoult 
<emphasis box="[247,296,1760,1786]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">et al</emphasis>
. 2022
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="52.[151,1436,1148,2041]" box="[199,707,1796,1823]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
Similar species. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kovacic &amp; Sanda" authorityYear="2016" box="[383,588,1796,1822]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Gobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="incognitus">
<emphasis box="[383,588,1796,1822]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Gobius incognitus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sarato" authorityYear="1889" box="[602,700,1796,1823]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Gobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fallax">
<emphasis box="[602,622,1797,1823]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">G</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[636,700,1796,1822]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">fallax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="52.[151,1436,1148,2041]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
Habitat. Infralittoral species, known from 
<quantity box="[692,767,1833,1859]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" unit="m" value="4.5" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="1.0">1–8 m</quantity>
depth from all kinds of rocky substrata: gravel, cobbles, boulders and bedrock, but on sand only when it is mixed with a hard substratum, never on pure sand. The substratum was bare or covered with short thallus algae (
<bibRefCitation author="Kovacic, M. &amp; Sanda, R." box="[658,925,1904,1933]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" pagination="1104 - 1124" refId="ref58613" refString="Kovacic, M. &amp; Sanda, R. (2016) A new species of Gobius (Perciformes: Gobiidae) from the Mediterranean Sea and the redescription of Gobius bucchichi. Journal of Fish Biology, 88, 1104 - 1124. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / jfb. 12883" type="journal article" year="2016">Kovačić &amp; Šanda 2016</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="52.[151,1436,1148,2041]" lastBlockId="53.[151,1437,151,249]" lastPageId="53" lastPageNumber="54" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
Geographic distribution. Presently known from the eastern coast of the Adriatic Sea, it is common from the Gulf of Trieste (
<bibRefCitation author="Tiralongo, F. &amp; Pillon, R." box="[274,557,1976,2003]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" pagination="215 - 220" refId="ref65266" refString="Tiralongo, F. &amp; Pillon, R. (2020) New distributional records of Gobius bucchichi from the Mediterranean Sea and in situ comparisons with Gobius incognitus. Annales, Series Historia Naturalis, 30 (2), 215 - 220." type="journal article" year="2020">Tiralongo &amp; Pillon 2020</bibRefCitation>
) to southern 
<collectingCountry box="[707,789,1976,2002]" name="Croatia" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Croatia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kovacic, M. &amp; Sanda, R." box="[805,1075,1976,2005]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" pagination="1104 - 1124" refId="ref58613" refString="Kovacic, M. &amp; Sanda, R. (2016) A new species of Gobius (Perciformes: Gobiidae) from the Mediterranean Sea and the redescription of Gobius bucchichi. Journal of Fish Biology, 88, 1104 - 1124. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / jfb. 12883" type="journal article" year="2016">Kovačić &amp; Šanda 2016</bibRefCitation>
); there is only one record in the Ionian Sea from Butrint, southern 
<collectingCountry box="[536,625,2012,2038]" name="Albania" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Albania</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kovacic, M. &amp; Sanda, R." box="[639,907,2012,2041]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" pagination="1104 - 1124" refId="ref58613" refString="Kovacic, M. &amp; Sanda, R. (2016) A new species of Gobius (Perciformes: Gobiidae) from the Mediterranean Sea and the redescription of Gobius bucchichi. Journal of Fish Biology, 88, 1104 - 1124. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / jfb. 12883" type="journal article" year="2016">Kovačić &amp; Šanda 2016</bibRefCitation>
), and a record in the Aegean Sea from Kondyli beach, eastern Peloponnese (
<bibRefCitation author="Tiralongo, F. &amp; Pillon, R." box="[484,777,151,177]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" pagination="215 - 220" refId="ref65266" refString="Tiralongo, F. &amp; Pillon, R. (2020) New distributional records of Gobius bucchichi from the Mediterranean Sea and in situ comparisons with Gobius incognitus. Annales, Series Historia Naturalis, 30 (2), 215 - 220." type="journal article" year="2020">Tiralongo &amp; Pillon 2020</bibRefCitation>
). Population from the Black Sea more similar in pattern of coloration to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Steindachner" authorityYear="1870" box="[337,482,187,213]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Gobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bucchichi">
<emphasis box="[337,357,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">G</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[373,482,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">bucchichi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
than to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kovacic &amp; Sanda" authorityYear="2016" box="[578,731,187,213]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Gobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="incognitus">
<emphasis box="[578,598,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">G</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[614,731,187,212]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">incognitus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in absence of black dot at the corner of mouth and any mark ventrally on iris (
<bibRefCitation author="Vasil'eva, E. D." box="[343,515,223,249]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" refId="ref65796" refString="Vasil'eva, E. D. (2007) Fish of the Black Sea. Key to marine, brackish-water, euryhaline, and anadromous species with color illustrations, collected by S. V. Bogorodsky. VNIRO Publishing, Moscow, 237 pp. [in Russian, with English abstract]" type="book" year="2007">Vasil’eva 2007</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Boltachev, A. R. &amp; Karpova, E. P." box="[527,840,223,249]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" refId="ref52296" refString="Boltachev, A. R. &amp; Karpova, E. P. (2017) Marine fishes of the Crimean Peninsula, second edition. Business-Inform, Simpheropol, 376 pp." type="book" year="2017">Boltachev &amp; Karpova 2017</bibRefCitation>
), and requires additional study.
</paragraph>
